text: Johan Sébastien Tatlot (born 26 March 1996 in Schœlcher) is a French tennis player. Tatlot has a career-high ATP singles ranking of World No. 226, achieved in September 2018. He also has an ATP career high doubles ranking of 525 achieved on 7 May 2018. Tatlot was the world no.5 junior ranked player in January 2014 and reached the 2014 Australian Open boys' doubles final. He received a wild card to advance to the doubles main draw in the 2015 French Open with doubles partner Tristan Lamasine, losing in the first round. ==External links== * * Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:French male tennis players Category:Sportspeople from Paris Category:People from Fort-de-France Category:French people of Martiniquais descent
